cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about using neural network models to automate the headline editing process for social media news writers. The paper focuses on using pre-trained language models and proposes a Self Importance-Aware (SIA) loss to address the different levels of editing in the dataset. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which are related to natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also involves training a neural network model, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and text generation, which could make it relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
